=== Octave packages ===

Octave's functionality (i.e. selection of functions available to the user in octave) is extended via octave-packages<ref>https://octave.sourceforge.io/packages.php</ref>, usually provided by octave-forge<ref>https://octave.sourceforge.io/</ref>. There are two ways to install octave packages:

* Use Octave's own {{C|pkg}} command to install missing packages (requires the <code>curl</code> USE flag)
* Use {{Package|app-portage/g-octave}} to generate ebuilds for octave-packages from Octave-Forge and install them via Portage

There is conflicting information about which method to prefer <ref>https://wiki.octave.org/Octave-Forge#Installing_packages</ref> <ref>https://wiki.octave.org/Octave_for_GNU/Linux#Gentoo</ref>, so no recommendation can be given at this point.

